T1  - The Organizational Impact of Profit Sharing
AU  - Florkowski, Gary W.
Y1  - 1987/10/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1987.4306712
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1987.4306712
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 622
EP  - 636
VL  - 12
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Few studies have evaluated the organizational impact of profit sharing. What research has been done suggests that profit sharers experience greater financial success, higher levels of productivity, and more positive employee attitudes. However, several methodological weaknesses of the studies seriously limit understanding of the full benefits and limitations of profit sharing. A model of profit sharing is presented to foster improved research.
AB  - Few studies have evaluated the organizational impact of profit sharing. What research has been done suggests that profit sharers experience greater financial success, higher levels of productivity, and more positive employee attitudes. However, several methodological weaknesses of the studies seriously limit understanding of the full benefits and limitations of profit sharing. A model of profit sharing is presented to foster improved research.
